WEBVTT

00:02.400 --> 00:03.700
You'reaving
Trouble breathing.

00:03.900 --> 00:06.300
That's a heart-related symptom
Called dyspnea.

00:07.200 --> 00:08.400
I wish you would have
Told me earlier

00:08.500 --> 00:10.200
That you were
Having trouble breathing.

00:10.300 --> 00:11.400
What does this mean?

00:11.500 --> 00:12.800
It means
That your wife's heart

00:12.900 --> 00:14.600
Is a little weaker
Than i'd like it to be.

00:14.600 --> 00:16.300
Is she still getting
A new liver?

00:16.500 --> 00:19.400
Her new lab results
Moves her up on the list.

00:20.800 --> 00:21.800
So...

00:22.900 --> 00:25.300
It's really just
A matter of time now.

00:25.700 --> 00:29.300
I'm making you
A nice sweater, too.

00:29.900 --> 00:31.700
I didn't forget you.

00:33.600 --> 00:35.700
If it looks anything
Like your husband's,

00:35.800 --> 00:38.300
Then i'll wear it proudly.

00:40.800 --> 00:43.400
Listen, there's
This really great jazz club

00:43.400 --> 00:44.400
On the south side,

00:44.400 --> 00:46.400
And i've got this friend
That's playing there tonight,

00:46.400 --> 00:48.800
If you maybe wanted
To go out or --

00:48.800 --> 00:49.800
What's up?

00:50.000 --> 00:52.000
Nothing...much.

00:52.700 --> 00:53.300
Mary and i
Were just talking

00:53.300 --> 00:55.000
About getting some drinks
On the south side.

00:55.000 --> 00:58.600
Oh, that sounds like fun,
If i'm not intruding.

00:59.200 --> 01:00.200
No.

01:03.500 --> 01:04.900
Hey.
Hey.

01:05.000 --> 01:06.400
How's miss crawford?

01:06.600 --> 01:09.000
If we don't get a liver
In the next 48 hours,

01:09.100 --> 01:10.500
Her heart's gonna give out.

01:11.500 --> 01:13.500
Vancouver,
How many times, man?

01:13.600 --> 01:15.300
What?
What did he do?

01:15.600 --> 01:17.400
He's eating my pecan pie.

01:17.700 --> 01:19.100
Did you label it?
Uh-huh.

01:19.100 --> 01:21.700
Yeah, why don't you put in
The order for miss crawford?

01:22.400 --> 01:25.400
Plan on sticking around, just in
Case you need to assist, okay?

01:27.600 --> 01:31.600
Eric: managing tech support --
Clients get disconnected,

01:31.600 --> 01:33.700
And they just go crazy.

01:33.800 --> 01:35.200
See, i focus on people,

01:35.600 --> 01:38.200
Instead of the technology
That's in front of them.

01:38.500 --> 01:40.000
Half the time they call,

01:40.200 --> 01:42.600
They just need some
Human connection.

01:44.500 --> 01:46.500
I think it's just a pager.

01:46.800 --> 01:48.600
You know, if it's bothering you,
I could put it away.

01:48.600 --> 01:50.400
No, no, no.
I don't even see it.

01:52.100 --> 01:53.000
I kind of long for the day

01:53.100 --> 01:55.200
When two people
Can just get together

01:55.200 --> 01:58.000
And communicate
Face-to-face.

01:58.400 --> 02:01.200
It's funny.
Mary talked you up.

02:01.600 --> 02:04.000
Said you were intelligent,
Beautiful.

02:04.000 --> 02:05.900
I thought, "yeah, right."

02:06.900 --> 02:08.900
But then you walked
Through thor.

02:11.300 --> 02:12.400
Well...

02:13.500 --> 02:13.900
Thank you.

02:13.900 --> 02:17.300
Listen, kate,
I've been out here, dating.

02:17.400 --> 02:19.200
I mean, you have no idea.

02:19.800 --> 02:21.200
No one's normal.

02:21.500 --> 02:24.600
But you -- there's something
About you

02:24.800 --> 02:29.800
That makes me want to just cut
Through all the white noise

02:29.900 --> 02:32.600
And ask you if you want
To come back --

02:32.600 --> 02:34.400
Uh...ooh.

02:36.400 --> 02:38.000
Hey, so,
I found the liver --

02:38.000 --> 02:39.500
Perfect match
For helen crawford.

02:39.500 --> 02:42.900
Where?
West virginia,
Hamilton county hospital.

02:42.900 --> 02:44.100
You sending vancouver?

02:44.100 --> 02:46.200
No, helen crawford
Is a nice woman.

02:46.200 --> 02:47.700
I don't want
To take any risks.

02:47.700 --> 02:49.200
Been there before?
Nope.

02:49.200 --> 02:52.300
It's fairly rudimentary.
You better bring equipment.

02:52.300 --> 02:54.800
I'm gonna ride down with kate.
Are you cool with that?

02:55.200 --> 02:56.000
Why wouldn't i be?

02:56.000 --> 02:58.400
Somebody help us!
We need some help!

02:58.500 --> 03:00.300
Somebody!
She collapsed.

03:00.300 --> 03:02.800
She -- she collapsed
In church.

03:02.900 --> 03:04.000
She just collapsed.

03:05.900 --> 03:08.400
Pulse, 129,
B.p., 82 over 48.

03:08.500 --> 03:09.700
Panels are up.
She's diaphoretic.

03:09.700 --> 03:12.300
Rashes and spider angioma
On bilat extremities.

03:12.300 --> 03:14.100
She missed
Her last appointment.

03:14.200 --> 03:15.900
All right,
Let's get her stabilized.

03:15.900 --> 03:17.600
Start her on zosyn,
Empirically.

03:18.300 --> 03:19.500
Shouldn't be happening.

03:20.600 --> 03:22.700
I'm looking at the blood work
From her last exam.

03:22.800 --> 03:23.800
This should not be happening.

