03:44.500 --> 03:46.100
Kate: and all he kept talking
About was technology

03:46.100 --> 03:48.000
And how it was desensitizing
People towards one another.

03:48.000 --> 03:51.300
Yeah, i bet you 10 bucks
You put your pager on the table.

03:52.300 --> 03:53.400
Why would you say that?

03:53.400 --> 03:54.600
Did you?

03:54.700 --> 03:56.000
What does that have to do
With anything?

03:56.000 --> 03:58.600
You sit there, you put
Your pager on the table,

03:58.600 --> 04:00.100
What does that say
To the poor guy?

04:00.200 --> 04:01.300
That i'm on call.

04:01.300 --> 04:03.200
Or that you're
Not interested.

04:04.100 --> 04:05.000
Give him a break.

04:05.000 --> 04:07.100
He was just trying to let you
Know that he likes you.

04:07.100 --> 04:10.000
He basically moved right past
Telling me he liked me.

04:10.000 --> 04:11.600
You forced his hand.

04:12.200 --> 04:15.500
You set the pager there.
You stare into space.

04:15.500 --> 04:17.800
I mean, come on.
He had to pull out the big gun.

04:17.800 --> 04:19.700
You're saying
It's my fault.

04:19.700 --> 04:22.800
Hey, i'm just saying --
I call it like i see it.

04:24.500 --> 04:26.200
West virginia radio.

04:26.300 --> 04:28.500
Yeah, i know.
I'll turn it off.

04:28.500 --> 04:32.000
So, listen, if you don't
Like this guy, why?

04:32.000 --> 04:36.500
I mean, mary told me that
He's great-looking, good job.

04:36.500 --> 04:38.800
I don't know. I don't think
He's really my type.

04:39.000 --> 04:40.300
So, what are you
Looking for?

04:41.000 --> 04:44.800
I don't know
If i'm looking for anyone.

04:46.000 --> 04:49.000
Okay, let's say
You're looking for someone.

04:49.000 --> 04:51.100
Oh, i don't know.

04:51.400 --> 04:55.000
Someone who didn't

04:55.000 --> 04:57.100
At a fancy restaurant
On a night like tonight.

04:58.600 --> 04:59.900
A night like tonight.

05:00.700 --> 05:01.900
A rainy night.

05:06.100 --> 05:08.100
Yeah, you know,
A rainy night.

05:11.300 --> 05:13.700
Okay, all right,
Car accidents.

05:13.800 --> 05:15.700
Car accidents
And dead people.

05:15.700 --> 05:17.000
See?
You get it.

05:17.700 --> 05:20.000
Well, you wouldn't want
Another one of us.

05:25.100 --> 05:29.300
No, i wouldn't want
Another one of you.

05:30.500 --> 05:32.300
But i don't want
A civilian, either.

05:32.300 --> 05:33.000
Ah.

05:34.300 --> 05:35.500
Copy that.

05:43.900 --> 05:45.200
Nate:
Well, as some of you know,

05:45.200 --> 05:48.700
Emily diaz-turner
Has autoimmune hepatitis.

05:48.700 --> 05:51.100
She spent the last three years
On the unos list

05:51.100 --> 05:52.600
Waiting for a new liver.

05:53.100 --> 05:56.400
Now it seems she has taken
Matters into her own hands

05:57.200 --> 05:59.600
And has received
An illegal organ transplant.

05:59.600 --> 06:00.700
Can we still help her?

06:00.700 --> 06:02.200
Well, that's our call,
Ultimately,

06:02.200 --> 06:04.100
But as dr. Newel
Will attest to,

06:04.100 --> 06:06.700
There are 79 current
Liver candidates

06:06.700 --> 06:08.400
In his chronic care department.

06:08.400 --> 06:12.100
It's a question of the acuity
Of our other patients.

06:12.600 --> 06:14.000
It's a question
Of fairness.

06:14.100 --> 06:16.600
Neither dr. Newel nor i
Want to turn her away,

06:16.600 --> 06:18.600
But we can't create
An unfair playing field

06:18.700 --> 06:20.400
For our other patients,
Either.

06:25.000 --> 06:26.300
Anything else?

06:26.900 --> 06:32.700
Yes, we also need
Your signatures here and here.

06:43.800 --> 06:47.300
Dr. Jonas,
This is mr. And mrs. Grayson.

06:48.100 --> 06:49.900
Dr. Thomas jonas
Will be performing

06:49.900 --> 06:51.600
The recovery surgery today.

07:11.200 --> 07:12.500
This room closed
Or something?

07:12.500 --> 07:13.500
It's for little kids.

07:13.500 --> 07:15.600
I know what it's for.
I've been coming here for years.

07:15.700 --> 07:17.100
I just want to know
If it's closed.

07:17.100 --> 07:18.900
What -- someone
In your family sick?

07:19.900 --> 07:20.800
My mom.

07:22.200 --> 07:23.900
I think she's gonna die.

07:36.900 --> 07:39.000
I've always wondered --
Who's st. Jude, anyway?

07:40.400 --> 07:42.700
Uh...some saint.
I don't know.

07:43.500 --> 07:46.200
There's a statue outside
That sort of explains who he is.

07:53.300 --> 07:54.400
Can i see?

07:58.600 --> 08:00.100
It's not any good.

08:00.100 --> 08:02.100
Come on, let me be
The judge of that.

08:08.000 --> 08:10.400
Wow.
These are intense.

08:20.400 --> 08:21.400
What?

08:22.900 --> 08:24.100
That's my dad.

08:29.800 --> 08:30.700
Okay.

08:31.100 --> 08:31.600
Thanks.

08:31.600 --> 08:33.900
I'll make sure i put her
Back together exactly like that.

08:36.200 --> 08:38.100
Let's get started.
Scalpel?

08:39.200 --> 08:40.200
Stop.

08:41.799 --> 08:43.200
Stop the procere.

08:43.600 --> 08:44.400
What?

08:45.000 --> 08:47.100
The graysons
Have changed their minds.

08:52.000 --> 08:52.900
Okay.

08:53.900 --> 08:55.200
What do you mean?

08:57.400 --> 09:00.600
I mean the graysons
Have changed their minds.

09:00.900 --> 09:02.800
Hold on. They were fine
When we walked in here.

09:02.800 --> 09:04.600
Why would they just
Change their minds?

09:15.000 --> 09:16.400
Because of me?

09:25.300 --> 09:26.900
Because of me.

09:34.200 --> 09:35.100
Hey.

09:37.200 --> 09:38.200
Hi.

09:39.100 --> 09:42.300
Have you seen my consultation
Notes from emily's last visit?

09:43.600 --> 09:45.800
I can have somebody
Dig them up for you.

09:47.400 --> 09:49.100
Someone must have known

09:49.500 --> 09:51.500
That she was planning
To go to mexico.

09:53.500 --> 09:55.100
Why do you think that?

09:55.200 --> 09:56.900
Because i can't find
My notes.

09:57.400 --> 09:59.800
You think someone here took
Your consultation notes?

10:00.200 --> 10:02.800
She needed them
For the surgery.

10:11.200 --> 10:13.400
Tom: oh, come on, kate.

10:14.000 --> 10:16.000
If i could change the color
Of my skin --

10:16.100 --> 10:17.100
Tom.

10:24.000 --> 10:24.800
So, what --

10:24.800 --> 10:28.300
Did they just take one look
At me and pull the forms?

10:36.600 --> 10:38.900
This is --
It's incredible.

10:46.400 --> 10:48.900
Do we have enough time
To get another surgeon?

10:50.300 --> 10:51.500
We can try.

10:53.300 --> 10:54.400
Okay.

10:57.100 --> 10:58.500
We'll keep her
On the respirator

10:58.500 --> 11:02.500
And, uh, get vancouver
Down here.

11:07.300 --> 11:11.100
Well, just go talk to them,
All right?

11:13.600 --> 11:14.900
Don't look at me
Like that.

11:14.900 --> 11:16.900
Just go talk to them,
Please, before they go.

11:45.400 --> 11:47.800
You know, i have
A daughter of my own.

11:48.800 --> 11:52.500
And if anything like this
Were to ever happen to her...

11:57.400 --> 11:59.600
I just can't tell you
How sorry i am.

12:01.300 --> 12:02.700
Thank you.

12:06.800 --> 12:08.600
We know
You've come a long way.

12:10.200 --> 12:12.400
We're sorry to have
Wasted your time.

12:14.500 --> 12:16.200
Mr. And mrs. Grayson,

12:16.400 --> 12:19.600
We can arrange
To bring another surgeon down.

12:19.700 --> 12:21.900
If you'll allow your daughter
To remain on the respirator,

12:21.900 --> 12:23.800
I can stay here with her.

12:25.200 --> 12:27.300
Been a terrible day.

12:30.100 --> 12:32.200
We just want
To take her home now.

12:32.700 --> 12:34.700
Um...
You don't want dr. Jonas

12:34.700 --> 12:36.300
To perform the surgery.

12:36.900 --> 12:38.200
We understand that.

12:38.200 --> 12:39.200
Ma'am...

12:40.200 --> 12:41.800
My daughter...

12:43.800 --> 12:46.600
Was shot
In a convenience store.

12:49.800 --> 12:52.400
We don't know who did it.

12:54.700 --> 12:57.900
But we do know
What kind he was.

13:04.700 --> 13:06.500
All we want

13:06.800 --> 13:10.400
Is to honor your daughter's
Decision to help us save lives.

13:11.500 --> 13:13.200
That's why we drove here
All night.

13:13.300 --> 13:15.600
That's why dr. Jonas
Will remove himself

13:15.600 --> 13:17.900
And i will stay here
For as long as it takes

13:17.900 --> 13:20.500
To get this right
For everyone involved.

13:43.000 --> 13:44.000
Hey.

13:45.700 --> 13:47.200
Dr. Grant.

13:48.300 --> 13:49.700
How did i get here?

13:49.700 --> 13:53.000
You lost consciousness.
Your husband brought you to us.

13:55.300 --> 13:57.400
I thought
I was going to die.

13:58.400 --> 14:00.700
I was sure
I was going to die.

14:01.600 --> 14:04.300
I can still see his face --

14:04.700 --> 14:06.000
Poor...

14:06.500 --> 14:07.800
Young...

14:08.700 --> 14:10.400
So young.

14:11.000 --> 14:13.900
He was just trying
To help his family.

14:14.500 --> 14:15.400
Who?

14:16.500 --> 14:18.400
The young man in mexico.

14:20.100 --> 14:21.500
You met your donor?

14:23.900 --> 14:27.000
After the surgery,
Asked to see him again.

14:28.200 --> 14:30.800
No one would look at me
In the eye.

14:30.900 --> 14:33.500
No one would speak to me.

14:34.900 --> 14:38.100
Later, after the surgery,

14:38.900 --> 14:40.900
I ularm
Whispering

14:41.900 --> 14:44.600
Saying the young man
Was dead.

14:46.000 --> 14:47.600
Simon: uh, dr. Grant?

14:50.700 --> 14:51.500
Yeah.

14:52.000 --> 14:53.900
I just got a call
From kate.

14:53.900 --> 14:54.600
What is it?

14:55.200 --> 14:56.900
The potential donor
In west virginia --

14:57.200 --> 14:59.300
They won't allow jonas
To recover the organ.

15:00.200 --> 15:01.200
What did he do?

15:01.300 --> 15:03.900
????

15:05.500 --> 15:06.600
Kate asked me to fly down.

15:06.600 --> 15:08.900
I have to ask for permission
To get a helicopter.

15:10.100 --> 15:13.200
Yeah, okay, call lifeflight
And get down there.

15:18.800 --> 15:20.100
What's happening?

15:21.300 --> 15:23.200
Mr. Crawford, i'm afraid
There's been a delay

15:23.200 --> 15:24.700
With the potential
Liver donor.

15:25.000 --> 15:27.700
Why?
We've sent a surgeon down
To perform the recovery.

15:27.700 --> 15:29.700
I thought you sent someone
Hours ago.

15:29.800 --> 15:31.300
Hang in there.ok

15:32.100 --> 15:33.700
As soon as a liver
Becomes viable,

15:34.000 --> 15:35.500
We'll start to prep her.

15:36.500 --> 15:37.600
I'm sorry.

15:54.400 --> 15:56.900
The tips procedure you performed
On mrs. Turner --

15:56.900 --> 15:58.400
I know you weren't
In favor of it.

15:58.500 --> 16:00.500
I just treat the patients.
You're the surgeon.

16:00.500 --> 16:02.700
But it did
Buy her some time.

16:02.700 --> 16:04.200
It also brought
Her meld scores down,

16:04.200 --> 16:05.900
Which lowered her status
With unos.

16:08.200 --> 16:09.900
Will my wife
Get another liver?

16:10.100 --> 16:11.000
Michael, what you did

16:11.000 --> 16:12.900
Goes against everything
We're trying to do here,

16:12.900 --> 16:14.300
Everything
That we believe in.

16:14.300 --> 16:16.500
Twice before,
Twice in three years,

16:16.500 --> 16:19.600
We've gotten that call
That you had a match for her.

16:23.500 --> 16:25.200
Each time, false alarm.

16:25.200 --> 16:27.600
You should have stayed here
And tried to work with us.

16:28.200 --> 16:30.300
Yeah, we started to believe
That, um...

16:30.800 --> 16:32.600
That was never gonna happen.

16:37.600 --> 16:38.800
It's a hard call.

16:38.800 --> 16:39.600
Yep.

16:40.500 --> 16:42.800
Half these people will die
On our waiting list.

16:42.800 --> 16:44.500
There's just not enough
To go around.

16:45.700 --> 16:46.900
It's not my department,

16:46.900 --> 16:50.600
But i wouldn't penalize
Ms. Turner for what she did.

16:53.100 --> 16:55.100
But it's not my department.

16:59.200 --> 17:00.600
Dr. Grant.
Hank carlson.

17:00.600 --> 17:02.600
Oh, yes, mr. Carlson.
How are you feeling?

17:02.600 --> 17:04.700
Well, my oldest daughter
Finally got pregnant.

17:04.700 --> 17:06.000
That's great news.

17:06.300 --> 17:08.099
Baby girl's due
In january.

17:10.300 --> 17:13.400
Dr.neexplained
My options.

17:13.400 --> 17:14.599
He told me
I could keep waiting

17:14.599 --> 17:17.000
Or talk toou
About some procedure.

17:18.099 --> 17:18.800
Right.

17:20.300 --> 17:21.300
I just want to know --

17:21.300 --> 17:24.000
Am i gonna live
To see my granddaughter?

17:27.300 --> 17:30.400
Why don't you come see me?
We can talk about your options.

17:30.900 --> 17:31.600
Do you understand

17:31.600 --> 17:33.500
What dr. Newel has been
Telling you?

17:34.000 --> 17:35.400
Basically,
It comes down to the fact

17:35.400 --> 17:37.200
That i'm getting worse.

17:37.700 --> 17:38.700
The blockage in the vein

17:38.700 --> 17:40.000
That brings the blood flow
To your liver

17:40.000 --> 17:42.900
Creates an accumulation
Of fluid in the abdomen.

17:43.900 --> 17:45.300
Believe me, i know.

17:45.400 --> 17:47.600
We can place a tube
In the middle of your liver

17:47.600 --> 17:49.400
To re-route
Your blood flow.

17:49.700 --> 17:50.700
But it won't cure me.

17:50.700 --> 17:53.000
No, it only
Buys you time.

17:54.600 --> 17:56.800
But i won't be
On the transplant list

17:56.800 --> 17:58.500
Until i get sick again.

17:59.300 --> 18:00.700
That's the trade.

18:09.600 --> 18:12.700
Ve always made'
My own decisions,

18:12.700 --> 18:15.000
The difficult ones,
All my life --

18:15.300 --> 18:19.300
In the army, with my family,
For my kids.

18:23.600 --> 18:26.500
You strike me as the kind of man
Who understands that.

18:27.100 --> 18:29.500
If you were me --
You had little time to live

18:29.500 --> 18:31.600
And a grandchild
On the way --

18:32.000 --> 18:34.500
Would you trade you a chance
At 10 years

18:34.500 --> 18:36.400
For the certainty
Of six months?

18:38.600 --> 18:41.400
As your doctor, i can only
Present you with the options.

18:41.400 --> 18:43.100
I can't make the decision.

